+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HAjHnrE9gMfBukMt8n4sYg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01HTuhgBAZgAnmG8FtVjRDrH","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-ssg-plugins.md","content":"# SSG Toolkit Plugins Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Implement 8 plugins for the SSG toolkit, each conforming to the `Plugin` interface with proper dependency declarations and hook implementations.\n\n**Architecture:** Each plugin is a separate file in `src/plugins/` exporting a `createXxxPlugin()` factory. Plugins use `transformContent`, `beforeBuild`, and/or `afterBuild` hooks. Data is shared between plugins via `ctx.data` Map. Wave 1 plugins have no deps, Wave 2 depends on Wave 1, Wave 3 depends on Wave 2.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript (strict, ESM with Node16 resolution), `marked` library for markdown parsing, vitest for testing.\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: markdown-ext plugin\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/plugins/markdown-ext.ts`\n- Test: `tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts` (existing, 8 tests)\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Marked } from 'marked';\nimport { Plugin, ContentFile, BuildContext } from '../core/types.js';\n\nexport function createMarkdownExtPlugin(): Plugin {\n  return {\n    name: 'markdown-ext',\n    version: '1.0.0',\n    dependencies: [],\n    hooks: {\n      transformContent(file: ContentFile, _ctx: BuildContext): ContentFile {\n        let content = file.content;\n\n        // Process admonition containers before markdown parsing\n        content = content.replace(\n          /^:::(note|warning|tip)\\n([\\s\\S]*?)^:::/gm,\n          (_match, type, body) => {\n            return `<div class=\"admonition admonition-${type}\">\\n${body.trim()}\\n</div>`;\n          }\n        );\n\n        // Extract footnote definitions\n        const footnotes: Map<string, string> = new Map();\n        content = content.replace(\n          /^\\[\\^(\\d+)\\]:\\s*(.+)$/gm,\n          (_match, id, text) => {\n            footnotes.set(id, text);\n            return '';\n          }\n        );\n\n        // Replace footnote references\n        content = content.replace(\n          /\\[\\^(\\d+)\\]/g,\n          (_match, id) => `<sup><a href=\"#fn-${id}\">${id}</a></sup>`\n        );\n\n        // Parse markdown to HTML using marked\n        const marked = new Marked();\n        content = marked.parse(content, { async: false }) as string;\n\n        // Append footnotes section\n        if (footnotes.size > 0) {\n          let section = '<section class=\"footnotes\"><ol>';\n          for (const [id, text] of footnotes) {\n            section += `<li id=\"fn-${id}\">${text}</li>`;\n          }\n          section += '</ol></section>';\n          content += section;\n        }\n\n        return { ...file, content };\n      },\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Verify:** `npx vitest run tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts`\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: asset-pipeline plugin\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/plugins/asset-pipeline.ts`\n- Test: `tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts` (existing, 8 tests)\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Plugin, ContentFile, BuildContext } from '../core/types.js';\n\nexport function createAssetPipelinePlugin(): Plugin {\n  return {\n    name: 'asset-pipeline',\n    version: '1.0.0',\n    dependencies: [],\n    hooks: {\n      transformContent(file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext): ContentFile {\n        const manifest = (ctx.data.get('asset-manifest') as { assets: string[] }) || { assets: [] };\n\n        // Match src=\"./...\" and href=\"./...\"\n        const rewritten = file.content.replace(\n          /(src|href)=\"\\.\\/([^\"]+)\"/g,\n          (_match, attr, path) => {\n            if (!manifest.assets.includes(path)) {\n              manifest.assets.push(path);\n            }\n            return `${attr}=\"/assets/${path}\"`;\n          }\n        );\n\n        ctx.data.set('asset-manifest', manifest);\n        return { ...file, content: rewritten };\n      },\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Verify:** `npx vitest run tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts`\n\n---\n\n## Task 3: syntax-highlight plugin\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/plugins/syntax-highlight.ts`\n- Test: `tests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts` (existing, 8 tests)\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Plugin, ContentFile, BuildContext } from '../core/types.js';\n\nexport function createSyntaxHighlightPlugin(): Plugin {\n  return {\n    name: 'syntax-highlight',\n    version: '1.0.0',\n    dependencies: [],\n    hooks: {\n      transformContent(file: ContentFile, _ctx: BuildContext): ContentFile {\n        // Only match <pre><code class=\"language-xxx\"> blocks\n        const content = file.content.replace(\n          /<pre><code class=\"language-(\\w+)\">([\\s\\S]*?)<\\/code><\\/pre>/g,\n          (_match, lang, code) => {\n            return `<pre data-language=\"${lang}\"><code class=\"language-${lang} highlighted\">${code}</code></pre>`;\n          }\n        );\n        return { ...file, content };\n      },\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Verify:** `npx vitest run tests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts`\n\n---\n\n## Task 4: taxonomy plugin\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/plugins/taxonomy.ts`\n- Test: `tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts` (existing, 8 tests)\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Plugin, BuildContext, ContentFile } from '../core/types.js';\n\nexport function createTaxonomyPlugin(): Plugin {\n  return {\n    name: 'taxonomy',\n    version: '1.0.0',\n    dependencies: [],\n    hooks: {\n      beforeBuild(ctx: BuildContext): void {\n        const tagMap = new Map<string, ContentFile[]>();\n        for (const file of ctx.files) {\n          if (file.tags) {\n            for (const tag of file.tags) {\n              const normalized = tag.toLowerCase();\n              const list = tagMap.get(normalized) || [];\n              list.push(file);\n              tagMap.set(normalized, list);\n            }\n          }\n        }\n        ctx.data.set('taxonomy-tags', tagMap);\n      },\n      afterBuild(ctx: BuildContext): void {\n        const tagMap = ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags') as Map<string, ContentFile[]>;\n        if (!tagMap) return;\n        for (const [tag, files] of tagMap) {\n          const items = files.map(f => `<li>${f.title}</li>`).join('\\n');\n          const html = `<h1>Tag: ${tag}</h1>\\n<ul>\\n${items}\\n</ul>`;\n          ctx.output.set(`tags/${tag}.html`, html);\n        }\n      },\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Verify:** `npx vitest run tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts`\n\n---\n\n## Task 5: rss-feed plugin\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/plugins/rss-feed.ts`\n- Test: `tests/plugins/rss-feed.test.ts` (existing, 7 tests)\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Plugin, BuildContext, ContentFile } from '../core/types.js';\n\nexport function createRssFeedPlugin(): Plugin {\n  return {\n    name: 'rss-feed',\n    version: '1.0.0',\n    dependencies: ['markdown-ext', 'taxonomy'],\n    hooks: {\n      afterBuild(ctx: BuildContext): void {\n        const tagMap = ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags') as Map<string, ContentFile[]> | undefined;\n\n        // Sort files by date, newest first; undated at end\n        const sorted = [...ctx.files].sort((a, b) => {\n          if (!a.date && !b.date) return 0;\n          if (!a.date) return 1;\n          if (!b.date) return -1;\n          return new Date(b.date).getTime() - new Date(a.date).getTime();\n        });\n\n        const items = sorted.map(file => {\n          let categories = '';\n          if (file.tags) {\n            categories = file.tags.map(t => `      <category>${t}</category>`).join('\\n');\n          } else if (tagMap) {\n            // Check taxonomy map for tags\n            const fileTags: string[] = [];\n            for (const [tag, files] of tagMap) {\n              if (files.some(f => f.slug === file.slug)) {\n                fileTags.push(tag);\n              }\n            }\n            if (fileTags.length > 0) {\n              categories = fileTags.map(t => `      <category>${t}</category>`).join('\\n');\n            }\n          }\n\n          const pubDate = file.date ? `      <pubDate>${file.date}</pubDate>\\n` : '';\n\n          return `    <item>\n      <title>${file.title}</title>\n      <link>${ctx.config.baseUrl}/${file.slug}.html</link>\n${pubDate}      <description><![CDATA[${file.content}]]></description>\n${categories}\n    </item>`;\n        }).join('\\n');\n\n        const feed = `<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<rss version=\"2.0\">\n  <channel>\n    <title>${ctx.config.title}</title>\n    <link>${ctx.config.baseUrl}</link>\n    <description>${ctx.config.title} RSS Feed</description>\n${items}\n  </channel>\n</rss>`;\n\n        ctx.output.set('feed.xml', feed);\n      },\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Verify:** `npx vitest run tests/plugins/rss-feed.test.ts`\n\n---\n\n## Task 6: search-index plugin\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/plugins/search-index.ts`\n- Test: `tests/plugins/search-index.test.ts` (existing, 7 tests)\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Plugin, BuildContext } from '../core/types.js';\n\nfunction stripHtml(html: string): string {\n  return html.replace(/<[^>]*>/g, '').trim();\n}\n\nexport function createSearchIndexPlugin(): Plugin {\n  return {\n    name: 'search-index',\n    version: '1.0.0',\n    dependencies: ['markdown-ext', 'syntax-highlight'],\n    hooks: {\n      afterBuild(ctx: BuildContext): void {\n        const index = ctx.files.map(file => {\n          const entry: Record<string, unknown> = {\n            title: file.title,\n            slug: file.slug,\n            content: stripHtml(file.content),\n          };\n          if (file.tags) {\n            entry.tags = file.tags;\n          }\n          return entry;\n        });\n        ctx.output.set('search-index.json', JSON.stringify(index));\n      },\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Verify:** `npx vitest run tests/plugins/search-index.test.ts`\n\n---\n\n## Task 7: sitemap plugin\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/plugins/sitemap.ts`\n- Test: `tests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts` (existing, 7 tests)\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Plugin, BuildContext } from '../core/types.js';\n\nexport function createSitemapPlugin(): Plugin {\n  return {\n    name: 'sitemap',\n    version: '1.0.0',\n    dependencies: ['taxonomy', 'rss-feed'],\n    hooks: {\n      afterBuild(ctx: BuildContext): void {\n        const baseUrl = ctx.config.baseUrl;\n        const urls: string[] = [];\n\n        for (const key of ctx.output.keys()) {\n          if (key === 'sitemap.xml') continue;\n          urls.push(`  <url><loc>${baseUrl}/${key}</loc></url>`);\n        }\n\n        const sitemap = `<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<urlset xmlns=\"http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9\">\n${urls.join('\\n')}\n</urlset>`;\n\n        ctx.output.set('sitemap.xml', sitemap);\n      },\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Verify:** `npx vitest run tests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts`\n\n---\n\n## Task 8: dev-server plugin\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/plugins/dev-server.ts`\n- Test: `tests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts` (existing, 7 tests)\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Plugin, BuildContext } from '../core/types.js';\n\ninterface DevServerConfig {\n  port: number;\n  routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;\n  assetPaths: string[];\n  searchIndexPath: string;\n}\n\nexport function createDevServerPlugin(): Plugin {\n  return {\n    name: 'dev-server',\n    version: '1.0.0',\n    dependencies: ['asset-pipeline', 'search-index'],\n    hooks: {\n      afterBuild(ctx: BuildContext): void {\n        const manifest = ctx.data.get('asset-manifest') as { assets: string[] } | undefined;\n        const assetPaths = manifest ? manifest.assets : [];\n        const routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }> = [];\n\n        // Asset routes\n        for (const asset of assetPaths) {\n          routes.push({ path: `/assets/${asset}`, handler: 'asset' });\n        }\n\n        // Content routes\n        for (const key of ctx.output.keys()) {\n          if (key.endsWith('.html')) {\n            routes.push({ path: `/${key}`, handler: 'static' });\n          }\n        }\n\n        // Search index path\n        const searchIndexPath = ctx.output.has('search-index.json') ? '/search-index.json' : '';\n\n        const config: DevServerConfig = {\n          port: 3000,\n          routes,\n          assetPaths,\n          searchIndexPath,\n        };\n\n        ctx.data.set('dev-server-config', config);\n      },\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Verify:** `npx vitest run tests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts`\n\n---\n\n## Task 9: Run full validation\n\n**Steps:**\n1. `npm test` — all 75 tests pass\n2. `npm run build` — TypeScript compiles clean\n3. `npm run lint` — no errors\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":120,"cache_read_input_tokens":38334,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":120},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"62ccdf36-8da7-4430-b652-b1a4a51f4081","uuid":"f0efcc5e-1dba-425d-a30e-76b7bd151074"}
